[SIZE=6][B]LeafTreeGen[/B][/SIZE]

Procedural, biome-aware custom trees that generate through vanilla worldgen.

LeafTreeGen adds dozens of hand-tuned and procedurally generated tree species. Every tree is baked into vanilla [ICODE].nbt[/ICODE] structure templates at startup and wired into jigsaw template pools, so placement is handled by the game's own worldgen pipeline rather than by runtime listeners.

[HR][/HR]

[SIZE=5][B]Features[/B][/SIZE]

[LIST]
[*][B]Biome-matched species[/B] - savanna acacias, dark-forest canopies, glacier pines, cherry groves, spiral-crown forests, and rainbow groves, each assigned to the biomes they fit
[*][B]Procedural engine[/B] - trees are generated in Java from per-species parameters (height, trunk shape, lean angle, canopy layers), so no pre-baked NBT files are required
[*][B]Jigsaw worldgen[/B] - the plugin generates a vanilla worldgen datapack on first load; Minecraft's structure system handles placement
[*][B]Plantable saplings[/B] - players can receive NBT-tagged saplings via [ICODE]/leaftree give[/ICODE] that grow into a random variant of the species when planted in a valid biome
[*][B]Reload command[/B] - [ICODE]/leaftree reload[/ICODE] rebakes all variants and regenerates the datapack
[*][B]Server-friendly placement[/B] - multi-block tree placement is timeboxed against a per-tick budget rather than run inline, so large trees don't stall the main thread
[*][B]Paper, Folia, Fabric, and NeoForge[/B] - one unified jar runs on Paper (and Folia builds), Fabric, and NeoForge, with full feature parity (worldgen, saplings, and the [ICODE]/leaftree[/ICODE] command) across every platform
[/LIST]

[HR][/HR]

